# Google Maps API Configuration
# 
# IMPORTANT: Get your API key from Google Cloud Console
# Visit: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 
# Required Steps (ALL MANDATORY):
# 1. Create a Google Cloud project
# 2. Enable billing (REQUIRED even for free tier - $200 monthly credit)
#    - Without billing, maps will NOT load
#    - Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/billing
# 3. Enable these APIs (CRITICAL):
#    - Maps JavaScript API
#    - Places API
#    - Geocoding API
#    - Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library
# 4. Create an API key in Credentials
#    - Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# 5. Configure API key restrictions (HTTP referrers)
#    - Add: http://localhost:3000/*
#    - Add: http://localhost:*/*
#    - Add your production domain when deploying
# 6. Copy your API key below (typically 39 characters)
# 
# See frontend/GOOGLE_MAPS_SETUP.md for detailed instructions
#
# CRITICAL: Billing must be enabled or you will see errors like:
# - "This page didn't load Google Maps correctly"
# - "Google Maps authentication failed"
# - "RefererNotAllowedMapError"
# - "ApiNotActivatedMapError"
#
# The application will automatically:
# - Validate your API key format
# - Check if required APIs are enabled
# - Retry loading if initial attempt fails (up to 3 retries with exponential backoff)
# - Provide specific error messages for troubleshooting
# - Detect ApiNotActivatedMapError and RefererNotAllowedMapError with fallback handling
#
# Production Mode:
# - Ensure the .env file is properly configured in your production environment
# - Verify the API key is correctly injected via VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY
# - Add your production domain to API key restrictions
#
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key_here
